<br>
As of this morning (Monday, 12/17/2001) we stood at 73,645 realm points.  This put us in 7th place in Midgard, with Einherjar having a comfortable lead over us at 87,550 and Warhost of the Aesir breathing down our necks at 70,825.  We are 21st on the server... within shooting distance of Nemesis (an Albion guild) with 79,901.  As I said, Warhost is right behind us.  After that, in all three realms, the next closest guild is quite distant.  Ahead of Nemesis, there are about 5 guilds in the 85-88K range, server-wide.  So, with some effort, we could get over the hump to score in the top 20.  With a LOT of effort we might get into the next tier of guilds.  Below the top 22 guilds, there is quite a drop-off.<br>
<br>
Saturday a week ago, when we had our big guild RvR night, we started the day at 28K and ended at 42K.  In the 8 days following, we made a pretty steady 4K realm points per day.  That should give you a sense of our prospects.  A few good nights could move us up pretty well.<br>
            -- Gisli<br>
